data.title: Aristocats Characters
data.text:
Madame Adelaide Bonfamille

1

Madame Adelaide Bonfamille is the owner of the aristocats. She first appeared in the Walt Disney movie The Airstcats voiced by Hermione Baddeley.

Luigi the Alley Cat

1

Luigi is a male cat and the accordeonist of the "Alley Cats" band. He is supposedly Italian.

Cyril the Alley Cat

1

Cyril is a male cat and the guitar player of the "Alley Cats" band. He is supposedly British.

Chino the Alley Cat

1

Chino is a male cat and the drummer of the "Alley Cats" band. He is supposedly Chinese.

Boris the Alley Cat

1

Boris is a male cat and the bass player of the "Alley Cats" band. He is supposedly Russian.

Amelia Gabble

1

Amelia Gabble is a female goose introduced in the film "Aristocats". She is a sister to Abigail Gabble. The two sisters tried to save O'Malley from drowning and befriended him and the Aristocats.

Abigail Gabble

1

Abigail Gabble is a female goose introduced in the film "Aristocats". She is a sister to Amelia Gabble. The two sisters tried to save O'Malley from drowning and befriended him and the Aristocats.

Roquefort

1

The mouse friend of the Aristocats. Named after the cheese of the same name. Note: for the Terrytoons mouse, see the entry "Little Roquefort."

Frou-Frou

1

Frou-Frou is a horse that appears in the film "The Aristocats"

Berlioz

1

The youngest kitten of Dutchess the cat, and owned by Madame Adelaide. One of the Aristocats.

Toulouse

1

The oldest kitten of Dutchess the cat, and owned by Madame Adelaide. One of the Aristocats.

Marie

1

The middle kitten of Dutchess the cat, and owned by Madame Adelaide. One of the Aristocats.

Lafayette

1

Lafayette is a Basset Hound who appears in the film "The Aristocats".
